main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed at Robins A.F.B., Georgia, on September 17, 1952.
interesting points: The objects appeared as white lights with a distinct yellow cast,The sighting lasted for over 20 minutes,No sound was heard from the objects,At least eight witnesses confirmed the sighting,One of the observers was an Air Force officer currently on flying status.
witness description: One AF officer and one AF pilot in flying status among the witnesses
